737-47. This is not unlike the scene in Shakespeare, Tempest, Act iv, Sc. 1, where Iris, Ceres, and Juno (Nymphs) enter in pro- cession. Duff describes a kind of masque or pageant of the seasons which are used as an example of the regularity of natural pheno- mena. Observe how Lucretius inverts the natural order, which is Zephyrus, Flora, Cupid, Venus, Spring.
